Parliament, Wednesday, 05 September 2018 – The Joint Constitutional Review will tomorrow continue to hear oral presentations from stakeholders on submissions concerning a possible review of Section 25 of the Constitution, which would make provision for the expropriation of land without compensation. These presentations will take place at Parliament and emanate from the written submissions on the matter. The presentations will continue until Friday. Please find the link for the draft programme
	https://tinyurl.com/ycyuezhf which is subject to change. Details are as follows: 
	Date: Thursday, 06 September 2018
	Time: 10:00
	Venue: Committee Room E249, Second Floor, National Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CO-CHAIRPERSONS OF THE JOINT CONSTITUTIONAL REVIEW COMMITTEE, MR LEWIS NZIMANDE AND MR VINCENT SMITH For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
